<section class="problem-section section" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
			<div>
				<p class="context-line">The problem</p>
				<h2 id="problem-title">Your Hevy data is useful. Getting answers from it should be easier.</h2>
			</div>
			<p>
				Your training history contains the evidence, but answering a multi-part question still means opening
				old sessions, comparing numbers, and searching through routines manually.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="problem-scenarios">
			<article>
				<strong>Understand your progress</strong>
				<p>You want to know what improved over the last six weeks—not just view another workout list.</p>
			</article>
			<article>
				<strong>Find what you saved</strong>
				<p>You remember a routine or exercise but cannot remember where it lives in Hevy.</p>
			</article>
			<article>
				<strong>Log without guessing</strong>
				<p>You want to create or update a workout without inventing missing training details.</p>
			</article>
		</div>

		<p class="problem-section__transition">
			Instead of opening and comparing individual workouts, ask multi-week questions and receive an answer
			grounded in specific sessions.
		</p>
	</div>
</section>
